<subSubSection id="C3337ED3FFC6FFDCFCEEFDAFFA021E54" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B962D58FFC6FFDCFCEEFDAFFA021E54" blockId="8.[840,1479,516,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Distribution. From South Africa to Angola, DR Congo, and Tanzania; dry grassland, woodland, and thickets; 
<quantity id="4CD180BDFFC6FFDCFABEFD8BFA1E1E54" box="[1328,1454,544,566]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="1250.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="500.0">500–2000 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3337ED3FFC6FFDCFCEEFD96FAA2184D" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B962D58FFC6FFDCFCEEFD96FAA2184D" blockId="8.[840,1479,516,1071]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFCEEFD96FBA11E31" box="[864,1041,573,595]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtenstenii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFCEEFD96FBA11E31" box="[864,1041,573,595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Solanum lichtenstenii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFAC9FD96FA181E31" box="[1351,1448,573,595]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFAC9FD96FA181E31" box="[1351,1448,573,595]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. incanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being densely pubescent with long-stalked trichomes, but can be distinguished from it geographically and by its ridged young stems. In herbarium specimens 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFBCFFD3AFB0F1EC5" box="[1089,1215,657,679]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtensteinii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFBCFFD3AFB0F1EC5" box="[1089,1215,657,679]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. lichtensteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plants have a greyer tone than the yellowish green 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFBB6FD06FB241EA1" box="[1080,1172,685,707]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFBB6FD06FB241EA1" box="[1080,1172,685,707]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. incanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this character is difficult to quantify. Individuals of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFBA1FD62FB1A1EBD" box="[1071,1194,713,735]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtensteinii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFBA1FD62FB1A1EBD" box="[1071,1194,713,735]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. lichtensteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in upland dry areas of South Africa can be of very small stature, with reduced entire leaves, while 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFC0CFCAAFC6F1F75" box="[898,991,769,791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFC0CFCAAFC6F1F75" box="[898,991,769,791]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. incanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is more consistent in plant size (shrubs of ca. 
<quantity id="4CD180BDFFC6FFDCFA17FCAAFA701F75" box="[1433,1472,769,791]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="1.0">1 m</quantity>
) and no dwarf forms are known. Lester and Hasan [
<bibRefCitation id="EFB850A9FFC6FFDCFACFFCB6FAED1F51" author="Lester RN &amp; Hazan SMZ" box="[1345,1373,797,819]" editor="Hawkes JG &amp; Lester RN &amp; Nee M &amp; Estrada N" journalOrPublisher="Kew: Royal Botanic Gardens Kew" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="369 - 387" refId="ref10927" refString="29. Lester RN, Hazan SMZ (1991) Origin and domestication of the brinjal eggplant, Solanum melongena, from Solanum incanum, in Africa and Asia. In: Hawkes JG, Lester RN, Nee M, Estrada N, editors. Solanaceae III: taxonomy, chemistry and evolution. Kew: Royal Botanic Gardens Kew, 369 - 387." title="Origin and domestication of the brinjal eggplant, Solanum melongena, from Solanum incanum, in Africa and Asia" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Solanaceae III: taxonomy, chemistry and evolution" year="1991">29</bibRefCitation>
] suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFCF9FC92FC441F2D" box="[887,1012,825,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtensteinii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFCF9FC92FC441F2D" box="[887,1012,825,847]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. lichtensteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(their ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFBCDFC92FB031F2D" box="[1091,1203,825,847]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">S. incanum</taxonomicName>
group D’’) had arisen from within ‘‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFC15FCFEFBBD1F09" box="[923,1037,853,875]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">S. incanum</taxonomicName>
group A’’ (= 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFB2FFCFEFAF41F09" box="[1185,1348,853,875]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campylacanthum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFB2FFCFEFAF41F09" box="[1185,1348,853,875]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. campylacanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and that 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFA3BFCFEFC3D1FE5" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="incanum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFA3BFCFEFC3D1FE5" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. incanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the strict sense arose from northern populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFA3BFCDAFC1C1FC1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtensteinii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFA3BFCDAFC1C1FC1" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. lichtensteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Phylogenetic results [
<bibRefCitation id="EFB850A9FFC6FFDCFB09FC26FB131FC1" author="Weese TL &amp; Bohs L" box="[1159,1187,909,931]" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="49 - 56" part="59" refId="ref10863" refString="27. Weese TL, Bohs L (2010) Eggplant origins: out of Africa, into the Orient. Taxon 59: 49 - 56." title="Eggplant origins: out of Africa, into the Orient" type="journal article" year="2010">27</bibRefCitation>
] show this not to be the case, 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFCC6FC02FC781FDD" box="[840,968,937,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtensteinii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFCC6FC02FC781FDD" box="[840,968,937,959]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. lichtensteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the South Africa 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFB77FC02FACB1FDD" box="[1273,1403,937,959]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linnaeaneum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFB77FC02FACB1FDD" box="[1273,1403,937,959]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. linnaeaneum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFA3BFC02FC601FB9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="campylacanthum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFA3BFC02FC601FB9" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. campylacanthum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sister to the rest of taxa sampled; this pattern of relationships is confirmed with a larger data set including more species of African solanums [
<bibRefCitation id="EFB850A9FFC6FFDCFBECFC56FBCD1871" author="Vorontsova MS &amp; Stern SS &amp; Bohs L &amp; Knapp S" box="[1122,1149,1021,1043]" journalOrPublisher="Bot J Linn Soc" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refId="ref11249" refString="38. Vorontsova MS, Stern SS, Bohs L, Knapp S (2013) African spiny Solanum (subgenus Leptostemonum, Solanaceae): a thorny phylogenetic tangle. Bot J Linn Soc, in press." title="African spiny Solanum (subgenus Leptostemonum, Solanaceae): a thorny phylogenetic tangle" type="book" year="2013">38</bibRefCitation>
] where 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFB43FC56FA981871" box="[1229,1320,1021,1043]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="umtuma">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFB43FC56FA981871" box="[1229,1320,1021,1043]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. umtuma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also part of a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFC6AFBB2FBD1184D" box="[996,1121,1049,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lichtensteinii">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFC6AFBB2FBD1184D" box="[996,1121,1049,1071]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. lichtensteinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C2956DBFFC6FFDCFB1BFBB2FABD184D" box="[1173,1293,1049,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linnaeanum">
<emphasis id="B95DF14AFFC6FFDCFB1BFBB2FABD184D" box="[1173,1293,1049,1071]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">S. linnaeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
